  user_input {
    user_response: "A web app integration https://chatgpt.com/s/t_6a5f1408ac888191943e4f070c846b47 If I were prompting **Codex, Gemini CLI, Claude Code, or Cursor**, I would avoid saying *\"make it better.\"* Instead, I\'d write a detailed engineering specification with explicit goals, constraints, technologies, and acceptance criteria.\n\nHere\'s the kind of prompt I\'d use:\n\n---\n\n# MASTER PROMPT\n\nYou are an elite frontend engineer, creative director, UX designer, motion designer, Three.js engineer, and scientific visualization expert.\n\nYou are NOT redesigning this website.\n\nYou are creating the world\'s most visually impressive interactive biology experience.\n\nThe current HTML project is only a starting point.\n\nYou have permission to completely rewrite, restructure, or replace every line of code if necessary.\n\nThe final result should feel like an Apple keynote demo, a NASA visualization, or a museum-quality interactive exhibit\342\200\224not a school webpage.\n\n---\n\n## Goal\n\nCreate the highest-quality interactive web experience possible for learning plant tissues (Xylem and Phloem).\n\nThe website should make users say:\n\n> \"I\'ve never seen an educational website this beautiful.\"\n\n---\n\n## Quality Target\n\nAim for the visual quality of:\n\n* Apple Vision Pro demos\n* Stripe.com\n* Linear.app\n* Spline\n* Figma\n* National Geographic interactives\n* NASA visualization tools\n* Rive animations\n* Award-winning Awwwards websites\n\nNOT:\n\n* textbook websites\n* Bootstrap layouts\n* ordinary dashboards\n* flat SVG diagrams\n\n---\n\n# TECH STACK\n\nRewrite the project using:\n\n* React\n* Vite\n* TypeScript\n* React Three Fiber\n* Three.js\n* GSAP\n* Framer Motion\n* GLSL shaders\n* Tailwind CSS\n* Zustand\n* Theatre.js\n* Leva\n* Postprocessing\n\nUse modern architecture.\n\n---\n\n# VISUAL DESIGN\n\nCompletely redesign every screen.\n\nUse\n\n* glassmorphism\n* depth\n* cinematic lighting\n* volumetric fog\n* HDR environments\n* bloom\n* ambient occlusion\n* soft shadows\n* animated gradients\n* premium typography\n* floating UI\n* microinteractions\n* physics-based transitions\n\nEvery interaction should feel expensive.\n\n---\n\n# 3D EXPERIENCE\n\nReplace flat SVGs with actual 3D models.\n\nInclude\n\n* full vascular bundle\n* xylem\n* phloem\n* cortex\n* epidermis\n* cambium\n\nUsers should be able to\n\n* rotate\n* zoom\n* pan\n* isolate tissues\n* explode layers\n* slice cross sections\n* reveal internal anatomy\n\n---\n\n# CAMERA\n\nCreate cinematic camera sequences.\n\nExamples\n\nLanding page\n\n\342\206\223\n\nCamera flies into stem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nCross section opens\n\n\342\206\223\n\nZoom into xylem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nWater starts flowing\n\n\342\206\223\n\nTransition to phloem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nSugar transport begins\n\nEverything should feel like Pixar.\n\n---\n\n# ANIMATIONS\n\nReplace CSS animations with professional motion.\n\nUse\n\n* GSAP timelines\n* spring animations\n* inertia\n* morphing\n* parallax\n* easing\n* motion blur\n* particle effects\n\nNo abrupt changes.\n\nEverything should be smooth.\n\n---\n\n# BIOLOGY SIMULATION\n\nCreate interactive simulations.\n\nWater transport\n\n* root pressure\n* cohesion\n* adhesion\n* transpiration pull\n* cavitation\n\nPhloem transport\n\n* source\n* sink\n* pressure flow\n* loading\n* unloading\n\nChanging environmental variables should immediately affect transport.\n\n---\n\n# PARTICLE SYSTEMS\n\nUse GPU particles.\n\nWater should\n\n* flow\n* accelerate\n* swirl\n* collide\n* refract light\n\nSugar molecules should\n* glow\n* move\n* split\n* merge\n* react to pressure\n# SHADERS\nWrite custom GLSL shaders\n* translucent cell walls\n* Fresnel highlights\n* subsurface scattering\n* animated gradients\n* procedural textures\n* glowing veins\nReplace cards with floating panels.\nUse\n* blur\n* transparency\n* depth\n* layered shadows\n* animated borders\n* neon highlights\nPanels should appear suspended in space.\n# MICROINTERACTIONS\nEvery element should have delight.\nHover\n\342\206\223\nlift\n\342\206\223\ntilt\n\342\206\223\nlight reacts\n\342\206\223\nparticles emit\n\342\206\223\nsound optional\n\n# STORY MODE\nCreate a guided experience.\nThe camera should automatically explain\n1. Plant anatomy\n2. Xylem\n3. Water transport\n4. Transpiration\n5. Phloem\n6. Sugar transport\n7. Comparison\n8. Quiz\nCompletely redesign quizzes.\nUse\n* animated transitions\n* achievement system\n* progress visualization\n* instant explanations\n* adaptive difficulty\n* celebration effects\n# PERFORMANCE\nMaintain\n60 FPS desktop\n\n30 FPS mobile\n\nLazy-load assets.\n\nUse instancing.\n\nOptimize shaders.\n\nOptimize textures.\n\nAvoid memory leaks.\n\n---\n\n# ACCESSIBILITY\n\nKeyboard navigation.\n\nReduced motion mode.\n\nResponsive.\n\nTouch controls.\n\nScreen reader support.\n\n---\n\n# CODE QUALITY\n\nWrite production-quality code.\n\nNo hacks.\n\nNo duplicate logic.\n\nNo inline styles.\n\nNo magic numbers.\n\nProper folder structure.\n\nReusable components.\n\nType-safe.\n\nDocument every major module.\n\n---\n\n# DELIVERABLES\n\nProduce:\n\n* complete React project\n* component architecture\n* 3D scene\n* animations\n* shaders\n* assets\n* documentation\n* comments\n* responsive layouts\n* optimized build\n\nThe final product should be portfolio-quality and capable of winning an Awwwards Site of the Day nomination.\n\n---\n\n## One suggestion\n\nIf you\'re using an autonomous coding agent like **Codex** or **Claude Code**, don\'t ask it to build everything in one run. Give it milestones such as:\n\n* Milestone 1: Project setup and architecture.\n* Milestone 2: 3D scene and camera.\n* Milestone 3: Biology simulations.\n* Milestone 4: Premium UI and animations.\n* Milestone 5: Polish, optimization, and accessibility.\n\nAgents tend to produce significantly better results when they can complete one well-defined milestone before moving to the next, rather than attempting an entire flagship application in a single pass.\n"
    items {
      text: "A web app integration https://chatgpt.com/s/t_6a5f1408ac888191943e4f070c846b47 If I were prompting **Codex, Gemini CLI, Claude Code, or Cursor**, I would avoid saying *\"make it better.\"* Instead, I\'d write a detailed engineering specification with explicit goals, constraints, technologies, and acceptance criteria.\n\nHere\'s the kind of prompt I\'d use:\n\n---\n\n# MASTER PROMPT\n\nYou are an elite frontend engineer, creative director, UX designer, motion designer, Three.js engineer, and scientific visualization expert.\n\nYou are NOT redesigning this website.\n\nYou are creating the world\'s most visually impressive interactive biology experience.\n\nThe current HTML project is only a starting point.\n\nYou have permission to completely rewrite, restructure, or replace every line of code if necessary.\n\nThe final result should feel like an Apple keynote demo, a NASA visualization, or a museum-quality interactive exhibit\342\200\224not a school webpage.\n\n---\n\n## Goal\n\nCreate the highest-quality interactive web experience possible for learning plant tissues (Xylem and Phloem).\n\nThe website should make users say:\n\n> \"I\'ve never seen an educational website this beautiful.\"\n\n---\n\n## Quality Target\n\nAim for the visual quality of:\n\n* Apple Vision Pro demos\n* Stripe.com\n* Linear.app\n* Spline\n* Figma\n* National Geographic interactives\n* NASA visualization tools\n* Rive animations\n* Award-winning Awwwards websites\n\nNOT:\n\n* textbook websites\n* Bootstrap layouts\n* ordinary dashboards\n* flat SVG diagrams\n\n---\n\n# TECH STACK\n\nRewrite the project using:\n\n* React\n* Vite\n* TypeScript\n* React Three Fiber\n* Three.js\n* GSAP\n* Framer Motion\n* GLSL shaders\n* Tailwind CSS\n* Zustand\n* Theatre.js\n* Leva\n* Postprocessing\n\nUse modern architecture.\n\n---\n\n# VISUAL DESIGN\n\nCompletely redesign every screen.\n\nUse\n\n* glassmorphism\n* depth\n* cinematic lighting\n* volumetric fog\n* HDR environments\n* bloom\n* ambient occlusion\n* soft shadows\n* animated gradients\n* premium typography\n* floating UI\n* microinteractions\n* physics-based transitions\n\nEvery interaction should feel expensive.\n\n---\n\n# 3D EXPERIENCE\n\nReplace flat SVGs with actual 3D models.\n\nInclude\n\n* full vascular bundle\n* xylem\n* phloem\n* cortex\n* epidermis\n* cambium\n\nUsers should be able to\n\n* rotate\n* zoom\n* pan\n* isolate tissues\n* explode layers\n* slice cross sections\n* reveal internal anatomy\n\n---\n\n# CAMERA\n\nCreate cinematic camera sequences.\n\nExamples\n\nLanding page\n\n\342\206\223\n\nCamera flies into stem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nCross section opens\n\n\342\206\223\n\nZoom into xylem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nWater starts flowing\n\n\342\206\223\n\nTransition to phloem\n\n\342\206\223\n\nSugar transport begins\n\nEverything should feel like Pixar.\n\n---\n\n# ANIMATIONS\n\nReplace CSS animations with professional motion.\n\nUse\n\n* GSAP timelines\n* spring animations\n* inertia\n* morphing\n* parallax\n* easing\n* motion blur\n* particle effects\n\nNo abrupt changes.\n\nEverything should be smooth.\n\n---\n\n# BIOLOGY SIMULATION\n\nCreate interactive simulations.\n\nWater transport\n\n* root pressure\n* cohesion\n* adhesion\n* transpiration pull\n* cavitation\n\nPhloem transport\n\n* source\n* sink\n* pressure flow\n* loading\n* unloading\n\nChanging environmental variables should immediately affect transport.\n\n---\n\n# PARTICLE SYSTEMS\n\nUse GPU particles.\n\nWater should\n\n* flow\n* accelerate\n* swirl\n* collide\n* refract light\n\nSugar molecules should\n* glow\n* move\n* split\n* merge\n* react to pressure\n# SHADERS\nWrite custom GLSL shaders\n* translucent cell walls\n* Fresnel highlights\n* subsurface scattering\n* animated gradients\n* procedural textures\n* glowing veins\nReplace cards with floating panels.\nUse\n* blur\n* transparency\n* depth\n* layered shadows\n* animated borders\n* neon highlights\nPanels should appear suspended in space.\n# MICROINTERACTIONS\nEvery element should have delight.\nHover\n\342\206\223\nlift\n\342\206\223\ntilt\n\342\206\223\nlight reacts\n\342\206\223\nparticles emit\n\342\206\223\nsound optional\n\n# STORY MODE\nCreate a guided experience.\nThe camera should automatically explain\n1. Plant anatomy\n2. Xylem\n3. Water transport\n4. Transpiration\n5. Phloem\n6. Sugar transport\n7. Comparison\n8. Quiz\nCompletely redesign quizzes.\nUse\n* animated transitions\n* achievement system\n* progress visualization\n* instant explanations\n* adaptive difficulty\n* celebration effects\n# PERFORMANCE\nMaintain\n60 FPS desktop\n\n30 FPS mobile\n\nLazy-load assets.\n\nUse instancing.\n\nOptimize shaders.\n\nOptimize textures.\n\nAvoid memory leaks.\n\n---\n\n# ACCESSIBILITY\n\nKeyboard navigation.\n\nReduced motion mode.\n\nResponsive.\n\nTouch controls.\n\nScreen reader support.\n\n---\n\n# CODE QUALITY\n\nWrite production-quality code.\n\nNo hacks.\n\nNo duplicate logic.\n\nNo inline styles.\n\nNo magic numbers.\n\nProper folder structure.\n\nReusable components.\n\nType-safe.\n\nDocument every major module.\n\n---\n\n# DELIVERABLES\n\nProduce:\n\n* complete React project\n* component architecture\n* 3D scene\n* animations\n* shaders\n* assets\n* documentation\n* comments\n* responsive layouts\n* optimized build\n\nThe final product should be portfolio-quality and capable of winning an Awwwards Site of the Day nomination.\n\n---\n\n## One suggestion\n\nIf you\'re using an autonomous coding agent like **Codex** or **Claude Code**, don\'t ask it to build everything in one run. Give it milestones such as:\n\n* Milestone 1: Project setup and architecture.\n* Milestone 2: 3D scene and camera.\n* Milestone 3: Biology simulations.\n* Milestone 4: Premium UI and animations.\n* Milestone 5: Polish, optimization, and accessibility.\n\nAgents tend to produce significantly better results when they can complete one well-defined milestone before moving to the next, rather than attempting an entire flagship application in a single pass.\n"
