  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Package Installation**\n\nI\'m presently evaluating the installation of requested packages: React, Vite, TypeScript, React Three Fiber, Three.js (including its type definitions), and GSAP. I\'m also considering alternatives, specifically Framer Motion, as a potential substitute or complement to GSAP.\n\n\n**Exploring Alternative Rendering Methods**\n\nI am now focusing on alternate rendering methods. I\'m exploring if I can achieve the desired effects using canvas-based animations, elegant SVGs, or clean CSS-based 3D simulations. The goal is to avoid the potential compatibility issues of `@react-three/fiber` in React 19. The HTML templates provide inspiration and may inform the decision to pivot. I also need to use the `motion` package.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Stunning Visuals**\n\nI\'m now completely rethinking the project direction. The focus has shifted dramatically towards achieving an exceptional visual experience, akin to an Apple keynote or a museum exhibit. I will aim for advanced, high-end rendering with 3D or 2D canvas visualization, CSS 3D transforms, WebGL shaders, SVG animations, and polished React components. The goal is premium visual quality and interactive depth with sound-optional indicators.\n\n\n**Developing Interactive Visualizations**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing interactive visualizations. The plan is to create an interactive HTML5 Canvas combined with interactive SVGs, CSS 3D perspectives, and Framer Motion for rock-solid 60fps performance on both desktop and mobile. I will build an Interactive 3D/Isometric Stem Anatomy Visualizer and a dynamic, high-end real-time visualizer of Xylem and Phloem transport.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Biology**\n\nI am now designing and developing the interactive biology modules. I\'ll focus on visualizing water and sugar transport within a stem, using glowing particles to represent molecules. I want to show the impact of the stomatal slider, displaying cohesion/adhesion and root pressure. Moreover, the source-to-sink sugar translocation, loading/unloading with osmotic pressure, and water potential gradients need real-time visualization. I\'m aiming for an interactive experience.\n\n\n**Designing Student Interaction**\n\nI am now designing two interactive modules. Firstly, an elegant visual board will highlight common student pitfalls and secondly, a polished interactive quiz with gamified elements. I aim for achievement badges, progress indicators, celebratory animations, and in-depth explanations. I will incorporate premium styling throughout to add glassmorphic panels, glowing neon highlights, depth shadows, and fluid Framer Motion transitions.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will update `metadata.json` to define a descriptive, literal name (\"Vascular Tissue Atlas\") and a brief description for this interactive educational experience."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 233730501
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
