    thinking: "**Reviewing Data Source**\n\nI\'m now diving into the source data to ensure `/src/data.ts` can accurately represent xylem and phloem, create compelling story steps, craft effective quiz questions, and design exam traps. I\'m focusing on incorporating high educational value and beautiful descriptions, as well.\n\n\n**Analyzing Cell Composition**\n\nI\'m now refining the cellular details for xylem and phloem. I\'ve broken down each into their four cell types \342\200\223 Tracheids, Vessels, Xylem Parenchyma, Xylem Fibres, Sieve Tube Elements, Companion Cells, Phloem Parenchyma, and Phloem Fibres. I\'m focusing on enriching each cell\'s description for the UI, including structure details and key facts. I\'m also planning the story steps. I\'ve designed the first two steps: stem cross-section and water highway with xylem. I\'ve also defined some common traps.\n\n\n**Defining Transport Mechanisms**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the processes within xylem and phloem. I\'ve concentrated on \'transpiration pull,\' explaining the negative pressure created by water vapor loss from leaves, and how cohesion and adhesion enable the continuous water column. I\'m also describing the phloem as a living system for transporting nutrients, and explaining sucrose translocation driven by turgor pressure.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create the `/src/data.ts` file to store all the scientific data, including rich cell descriptions, story steps for our cinematic narration, exam traps, and the interactive quiz questions. This separates static content from the component logic, keeping our codebase clean and modular."
