  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing Atlas Success**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased to report that the `compile_applet` and `lint_applet` processes executed flawlessly. Now, I\'m shifting my focus to synthesizing the core essence of this biology atlas experience, encompassing its design, visual presentation, layout structure, and the underlying scientific information.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the interactive, state-of-the-art educational experience for learning plant vascular tissues (Xylem and Phloem). Here is a conceptual overview of what has been implemented:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Conceptual Design\n*   **Dual-State Environmental Lighting**: Seamless transitions between a classic, crisp **Archival Parchment Light Theme** (reflecting vintage scientific botany manuals) and an immersive **Bioluminescent Dark Theme** (featuring high-contrast glowing neon signals of water and sucrose flows).\n*   **Cinematic Camera Engine**: Implements smooth spring-physics interpolation to gently slide, zoom, and rotate views based on the reader\'s current topic\342\200\224mimicking professional keynote slides.\n*   **Aesthetic Pairings**: Features **Space Grotesk** for tech-forward headings, **Inter** for legible UI body copy, and **JetBrains Mono** for mechanical readouts.\n\n### \360\237\224\254 Core Scientific Simulation & Interactive Visualizers\n*   **3D Isometric Stem Wedge**: Features a rotating, touch-responsive 3D cross-section of an angiosperm stem showing distinct layers (Epidermis, Cortex, Phloem, Cambium, Xylem, and Pith) with hover descriptions.\n*   **Longitudinal Transpiration Pull (Xylem)**: Simulates the *Cohesion-Tension Theory*. Watch glowing green-blue water particles ascend under tension, wiggling laterally to show cohesion/adhesion forces, and vaporizing into a misty cloud at stomatal guard cells.\n*   **Munch Pressure-Flow (Phloem)**: Simulates translocation. Watch companion cells actively load golden sucrose hexagons, drawing water by osmosis to build turgor pressure that drives bulk sap flow to roots.\n*   **Dynamic Sliders**: Change stomatal aperture or sugar loading in real-time, instantly adjusting particle speed, density, and flow velocity indicators in millimeters per second.\n\n### \360\237\223\232 Curated Educational Content & Gamified Quiz\n*   **Complete Cellular Inventory**: Detailed interactive cards for each cell type (Vessels, Tracheids, Sieve-Tube Elements, Companion Cells, Parenchyma, and Fibres) complete with stylized, custom vector anatomy illustrations and structural statistics.\n*   **Examiner Pitfalls Warning Board**: Outlines classic student pitfalls (e.g., *Collenchyma vs Xylem Fibres* or *Living vs Dead Conduction*) in high-contrast callouts.\n*   **Gamified Diagnostic Quiz**: A 6-question challenge testing core mechanics and pitfalls. Includes progress tracking, celebratory particle splashes on correct choices, deep physiological explanations, and custom achievement badge unlocks (e.g., *Vascular Mastermind*, *Plant Physiologist*, *Junior Botanist*)."
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 298047243
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
